About the Film:
Johnny Worricker (Bill Nighy) is a long-serving MI5 officer whose closest friend is also his boss, 
the Director General of MI5, Benedict Baron (Michael Gambon). Baron distributes a potentially 
explosive report to Johnny along with Jill Tankard (Judy Davis) and the Home Secretary (Saskia Reeves). 
In that meeting, Worricker verbally highlights a note at the foot of page eight alleging that 
the Prime Minister (Ralph Fiennes) has details about the US government torturing prisoners in 
secret overseas prisons.

might have saved British lives.
